{
  "texts": [
    "Seasonal changes play a pivotal role in influencing solar cell temperature.",
    "During winter in cold climates, solar cells may encounter reduced efficiency due to the colder temperatures (Salamah et al., 2022).",
    "Cold weather can affect the performance of solar cells by altering the behavior of charge carriers and increasing resistive losses.",
    "On the other hand, in hot climates during the summer, solar cells may face thermal losses.",
    "The trade-off between seasonal variations and optimal performance highlights the importance of considering regional climatic conditions in solar energy system planning."
  ]
}